# Implementation Plan - Apple DFU/Reboot VDM

This plan adds support for Apple-specific Vendor Defined Messages (VDM) to trigger DFU and Reboot modes on Apple devices. These messages use SVID 0x05AC and are sent using the SOP'' DEBUG token.

## Proposed Changes

### USB-PD VDM Implementation
#### [MODIFY] [usbpd_vdm_user.h](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.h)
- Define Apple-specific constants:
  - `APPLE_SVID` (0x05AC)
  - `APPLE_CMD_PERFORM_ACTION` (0x12)
  - `APPLE_ACTION_REBOOT` (0x105)
  - `APPLE_ACTION_DFU` (0x106)
- Add prototype for `USBPD_VDM_SendAppleCommand`.

#### [MODIFY] [usbpd_vdm_user.c](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.c)
- Implement state tracking for pending Apple commands.
- Update [USBPD_VDM_SendSpecific](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/USBPD/Target/usbpd_vdm_user.c#447-464) to fill VDOs for `APPLE_CMD_PERFORM_ACTION`:
  - VDO1: Action ID (bits 15-0)
  - VDO2: Argument (bits 31-16)
- Implement `USBPD_VDM_SendAppleCommand` to initiate the request via `USBPD_PE_SVDM_RequestSpecific` using `USBPD_SOPTYPE_SOP2_DEBUG`.

### User Interface / Trigger
#### [MODIFY] [main.c](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/Core/Src/main.c)
- Implement button polling in [StartDefaultTask](file:///Users/leon/code/usb-pd-vdm/Core/Src/main.c#540-557).
- Trigger `USBPD_VDM_SendAppleCommand`:
  - Short press (< 1s) -> Reboot.
  - Long press (> 2s) -> DFU.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None (requires physical hardware and Apple device).

### Manual Verification
1. Connect the STM32 board to an Apple iPad.
2. Observe serial logs for successful PD negotiation (Explicit Contract).
3. Short press the user button:
   - Check logs for `[VDM] Port0: Sending Apple Reboot`.
   - Verify iPad reboots.
4. Long press the user button:
   - Check logs for `[VDM] Port0: Sending Apple DFU`.
   - Verify iPad enters DFU mode (screen stays black, but detected as DFU on a Mac).
